cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.DS, cs.MM

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image analysis and detection of polyps in computer tomographic colonography. It also involves the use of computer-aided detection, which is a common technique in computer vision. 

The paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it uses adaptive-scale candidate polyp delineation and classification based on new texture and geometric features. 

Information retrieval (cs.IR) is another possible sub-category as the paper involves the detection of specific features (polyps) within a larger dataset (colonography images). 

Data structures (cs.DS) is a less likely sub-category, but it could be relevant as the paper may involve the use of data structures to efficiently store and process the large amounts of data involved in colonography images. 

Multimedia (cs.MM) is another possible sub-category as the paper deals with the analysis of medical images, which are a form of multimedia.
